paragraphs.text:
%md 

# The Flink Streaming Interpreter Comes to Apache Zeppelin!!

**Note**: This is **_not_** officially supported yet. [ZEPPELIN-1416](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZEPPELIN-1416?filter=-1) and [PR-1409](https://github.com/apache/zeppelin/pull/1409)

# In this demo, we create a simple streaming application:
- ### Create a FilteredEndpoint to collect tweets with `ff16` or `flinkforward`
- ### Create a sliding window of 2 minutes with 30 second offsets
- ### Count the tweets in each window
- ### Sink the results to a text file 

# In the following paragraph, we will leveaage Zeppelin's build in Angular Charting capabilities to chart the interest in our topics over time.

result.msg:

paragraphs.title: Streaming Code
AngularJS Chart (Built in to Zeppelin)
paragraphs.text:
%flink

import  scala.io.Source

val twoMinCnt = Source.fromFile("/tmp/2minCounts.txt").getLines.toList


println("%table\ntime\tff_tweets\n" + twoMinCnt.zipWithIndex.map(o=> o._2+"\t"+o._1).mkString("\n"))
